Key Match Events: Quinton de Kock top scored with 65 as South Africa beat England by seven runs
Kagiso Rabada shifted the momentum with a brilliant over, picking up the wicket of Liam Livingstone and only conceding four runs
Post-Match Reflections: Aiden Markram expressed pride in the team's resilience after the close victory
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played in the T20 World Cup Super Eight
Others: England struggled to build momentum into their innings as Buttler, Bairstow and Moeen Ali all batted at slower than run-a-ball
